INT. RAHEIR’S WORKSHOP 

RAHEIR leads the PLAYER into his workshop. 
His daughter, FAYIRA, sits at a worktable, busy fashioning small parts for a large shield. 
Raheir strolls over to his seat and gestures at another for the player.
He looks around the table, moving some things with his hand as he murmurs to himself.

Without pausing, Fayira holds up a tool for him take from her hand. 
He smiles at her and looks at the player, obviously proud of her.

Fayira laughs and turns an imaginary key lock over her mouth.  

But the Player doesn’t sit—-they’re here for a reason.

As Raheir speaks, he and his daughter work in perfect synchronicity. 
He holds out a hand for a specific tool, and she knows which one to pass him without words exchanged.
Raheir glances at his daughter and back to the Player.
It’s like a record scratch in the room. Fayira gets ready to defend her dad. But Raheir interjects.
She stares at him thoughtfully before nodding and taking her leave.
The Player and Raheir stare at each other. Finally, the player relaxes and shakes their head no.
Suddenly, we hear screams from outside—-the sound of wood rending as the town is attacked.
